  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200°C (400°F).",
    "Rinse fish fillets and pat dry with paper towels.",
    "Place kombu slice on a baking sheet and lay fish fillets on top.",
    "Drizzle olive oil over fish and season with salt, pepper, cumin, coriander, and smoked paprika.",
    "Zest one orange and one lemon, then squeeze their juice over the fillets and sprinkle the zest evenly.",
    "Cover the sheet loosely with foil and bake for 12 minutes.",
    "Remove foil, stir in tahini with 1/4 cup water to make a silky sauce, and pour over fish.",
    "Return to oven for another 8 minutes until fish is flaky and sauce is glossy.",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley before serving.",
    "Serve hot with a side of steamed rice or couscous."
  ],
